The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                            A seven-year-old girl and her grandmother drowned in a pond in Domjur, Howrah, on Sunday morning. Police said Swastika Srimani fell into the pond while washing clothes on the bank. Her grandmother Kabita Pal dived in to save her. The girl, a resident of Cossipore, was visiting her grandmother. The bodies were fished out.    Teacher stabbed: Asim Basu, a 48-year-old primary school teacher, was stabbed by unidentified youths near his home on Netaji Subhas Bose Road in Howrah on Sunday evening. Basu, who was recently involved in a tiff with some youths, was admitted to a local hospital.																																																								  Road mishap: A man in his 30s was critically injured after being hit by a vehicle at the Maniktala crossing on Sunday afternoon. Police said the man was crossing the road when the mishap occurred. He was admitted to RG Kar hospital.                                                                                                                                               
